King William's Town A 40-year-old man has been arrested for allegedly murdering his girlfriend, police said in a statement on Tuesday.&nbsp; Police spokesperson Captain Jackson Manatha said the 39-year-old woman was murdered in the early hours of Monday morning, December 26, at the Yako informal settlement in Butterworth.&nbsp; Manatha said police believe the accused beat her to death with a stick. Her identify is being withheld until her family is informed.&nbsp; Manatha said the suspect will appear in the Butterworth Magistrate's Court on Wednesday, December 28. ANA